title: Iggy Azalea Ft. Rita Ora - Black Widow (2014 Single)
description:
03:29, 320 kbps, 2014

Recorded at: Record Plant and Westlake Recording Studios, Los Angeles; Jungle City Studios, New York

"Black Widow" is a song by Australian rapper Iggy Azalea, from her debut studio album, The New Classic (2014). The song's hook is sung by British recording artist Rita Ora, and its lyrics chronicle subjects of revenge and feminism in a failed romantic relationship. "Black Widow" was written by Azalea, Katy Perry, Sarah Hudson, Benny Blanco, and duo StarGate; the latter also produced the song. On 3 June 2014, Azalea confirmed "Black Widow" as the forthcoming fifth single from The New Classic, while also affirming the release of an accompanying music video for the song.
